cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the security of an image cipher based on transformed logistic maps and reports security flaws in most Logistic-map-based ciphers. This is a clear indication that the paper belongs to the Cryptography and Security sub-category.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the computational complexity of deciphering the image cipher and proposes a new method with lower complexity. This involves analyzing the information content of the cipher and plain-images, which falls under the purview of Information Theory.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a system for encrypting and decrypting images based on transformed logistic maps. This involves designing and analyzing a control system, which falls under the Systems and Control sub-category.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with encrypting and decrypting images, which is a multimedia application. This falls under the Multimedia sub-category.
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with image encryption and decryption, which is a computer vision application. This falls under the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition sub-category.
